Seed Processing and Bacterial Breeding
To protect the seed germination and to protect against fungal diseases in the seedlings, add 5 gm trichoderma after seeding or 2 gm of thyme 2 gm carbendazim and stir it to one per capita seed. After that, steam from the storage solution of one Pakota weighing 250 grams of Rhizobium bacterial culture to 1o kg seed.
